com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface FilterEntry


  • public interface FilterEntry
    An entry for a UPA FilterList that can house only other container types. FilterList is a non-uniform type, where the FilterList.containerType() should indicate the most common type housed in each entry. Entries that differ from this type must specify their own type via FilterList.containerType().
    See Also:
    FilterEntryActions, FilterEntryFlags, FilterList

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears FilterEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, FilterEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encodes single FilterEntry using the data provided. Typical use:
        1. Call FilterList.encodeInit()
        2. Call FilterEntry.encode() for each FilterEntry in the list using the previously encoded FilterEntry data
        3. Call FilterList.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeInit

        int encodeInit(EncodeIterator iter,
               int maxEncodingSize)
        Prepares FilterEntry for encoding. Typical use:
        1. Call FilterList.encodeInit()
        For each row in the FilterEntry using the same buffer perform steps 2, 3, and 4 below: 2. Call FilterEntry.encodeInit()
        3. Encode FilterEntry contents
        4. Call FilterEntry.encodeComplete()
        5. Call FilterList.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        maxEncodingSize - Expected max encoding size of the FilterEntry data
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes FilterEntry encoding. Typical use:
        1. Call FilterList.encodeInit()
        For each row in the FilterEntry using the same buffer perform steps 2, 3, and 4 below 2. Call FilterEntry.encodeInit()
        3. Encode FilterEntry contents
        4. Call FilterEntry.encodeComplete()
        5. Call FilterList.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • id

        int id()
        FilterEntry id. An ID associated with the entry. Each possible id corresponds to a bit-value that can be used with the message key's filter member. This bit-value can be specified on the filter to indicate interest in the id when present in a RequestMsg or to indicate presence of the id when present in other messages.
        Returns:
        the id

      • id

        void id(int id)
        FilterEntry id. FilterEntry id. An ID associated with the entry. Each possible id corresponds to a bit-value that can be used with the message key's filter member. This bit-value can be specified on the filter to indicate interest in the id when present in a RequestMsg or to indicate presence of the id when present in other messages. Must be in the range of 0 - 255.
        Parameters:
        id - the id to set

      • containerType

        the containerType
